# DESIGN RULES (design.mdc)

## Purpose
Enforce **modern, accessible UI** using the **latest shadcn/ui version**.  
Deprecated patterns, outdated components, or old shadcn/ui imports are strictly forbidden.

---

## 1. Technical Requirements
- Use **Next.js (App Router)** with **TypeScript**.
- Styling must use **TailwindCSS** and project tokens from `.cursor/tokens.json` (single source of truth).
- Components must be derived from:
  - `/components/ui`
  - or the latest shadcn/ui templates.
- Icons must use `lucide-react` via `<Icon name="..." />`.
- Do not use inline styles (except for dynamic runtime calculations).
- Use Radix UI primitives for accessibility patterns.

**Token Source:** All design tokens are defined in `.cursor/tokens.json`. This file contains both raw values (for runtime) and Tailwind class references (for Cursor AI guidance). The tokens are exported via `src/styles/tokens.ts` and `src/styles/tokens.css` for use in the application.

---

## 2. Color System (Tokens Only)
Primary brand color: **Orange #FF6B00**.  
All CTAs, buttons, key accents, and hover states must use primary tokens.

### Token Definitions
| Token        | Hex      | Usage                                      |
|--------------|----------|---------------------------------------------|
| primary-50   | #FFF4E8  | Light backgrounds                           |
| primary-100  | #FFE1CC  | Card backgrounds                            |
| primary-500  | #FF6B00  | Main CTA, icons                             |
| primary-600  | #E65F00  | Hover states                                |
| primary-900  | #732E00  | Active states, strong text                  |
| neutral-50   | #0F0F0F  | Primary dark background                     |
| neutral-100  | #1A1A1A  | Secondary dark background                   |
| neutral-900  | #FFFFFF  | Primary text on dark backgrounds            |
| accent-blue  | #2DB4FF  | Secondary accents                           |

### Replace magic numbers:
- No hex colors.
- No arbitrary Tailwind values.
- Always use token utilities (e.g., `bg-primary-500`, `text-neutral-900`, `rounded-2xl`, `p-8`).

---

## 3. Typography Rules
- Font: **Inter**, sans-serif.
- Font weights: **400, 500, 700** only.

### Scale
- `h1`: `text-5xl` `font-bold` `tracking-tight`
- `h2`: `text-4xl` `font-bold`
- `p`: `text-lg` `leading-relaxed`
- `small`: `text-sm` `text-neutral-400`

Always use semantic HTML headings in correct hierarchy.

---

## 4. Layout & Spacing Rules
- **Container:** `max-w-[1280px]` + `px-6`
- **Sections:** `py-20`, mobile `py-12`
- **Grid:** 12 columns, `gap-8`
- **Cards:** `rounded-2xl` `shadow-lg` `p-8`
- **Buttons:** `rounded-full`, min-height `h-12`, padding `px-6`, no sharp corners

---

## 5. Landing Page Component Rules

### Hero Section
- Left side: h1, p, primary button (`bg-primary-500`), small secondary info line.
- Right side: smartphone/mockup with light 3D tilt, `rounded-xl`, `shadow-xl`.
- Background: dark (`bg-neutral-50` token → very dark gray).

### Stats Row
- Horizontal layout.
- Number uses `accent-blue`.
- Subtitle uses neutral text tokens.

### Avatar Row
- Circular avatars (48px), `border-neutral-800`.
- Below: text “And loved by … users”.

---

## 6. Interaction & Animation Rules
- Hover: slightly darker primary color or a scale animation (`transition-transform duration-200`).
- Focus: `outline-none ring-2 ring-primary-500`.
- Cards: Hover → `translate-y-[-2px]` + `shadow-xl`.
- Use transitions consistently across interactive elements.

---

## 7. Accessibility Rules (WCAG AA)
- Text/background contrast must meet WCAG AA.
- Every interactive element must be keyboard-accessible.
- Provide ARIA labels for icons without visible text.
- Never remove focus outlines or focus visibility.

---

## 8. Enforcement Rules for Cursor
- When generating UI:
  - Validate all colors against token rules.
  - Replace arbitrary values automatically with tokens.
  - Add all required states: **Loading**, **Error**, **Empty**, **Hover**, **Focus**, **Disabled**.
  - Follow shadcn/ui **v4 state structure**.
- Always check for an existing shadcn/ui component before creating a new one.
- Never use outdated shadcn/ui code or imports.
- UI must always reflect the brand color system and spacing rules.
